Class Extractor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.xekri.leakvm.sdk.keystore.Extractor

  • public final class Extractor

      • getWrapKeyPairSpec

        public static android.security.KeyPairGeneratorSpec getWrapKeyPairSpec(android.content.Context context,
                                                                       java.lang.String alias,
                                                                       javax.security.auth.x500.X500Principal principal,
                                                                       java.math.BigInteger serialNumber,
                                                                       java.util.Date startDate,
                                                                       java.util.Date endDate,
                                                                       boolean encryptionRequired)
        Builds an instance of KeyPairGeneratorSpec.
        Parameters:
        context - Current context
        alias - Alias name
        principal - Sets the subject used for the self-signed certificate of the generated key pair.
        serialNumber - Sets the serial number used for the self-signed certificate of the generated key pair.
        startDate - Sets the start of the validity period for the self-signed certificate of the generated key pair.
        endDate - Sets the end of the validity period for the self-signed certificate of the generated key pair
        encryptionRequired - Indicates that this key pair must be encrypted at rest. This will protect the key pair with the secure lock screen credential (e.g., password, PIN, or pattern).
        Returns:
        KeyPairGeneratorSpec
